2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses reinforcement learning algorithms and their optimization, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
3. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper discusses the reduction of task complexity, which is a common problem in robotics. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the optimization of behavior in a variety of environments, which is a common problem in systems and control. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper discusses theoretical guarantees of the quality of behaviors derived from approximate abstractions, which could be relevant to programming language design and implementation.
